Blocks.childText: PSALMS 46-17-48-49, 49 1 23 1 1 1 5 6 6 (9. 7 5 5 1 2 1 12 6 6 5 5 6 7 7 -:-1- 3 -1--2--5 1-2 3 6 5 5 5 :1 Psalm XLVI. 1 God is our refuge and our strength, 10 Be still, and know that 1 am God: in straits a present aid. among the heathen I 2 Therefore, although the earth remove, Will be exalted ; I on earth we will not be afraid; will be exalted high. Though hills amidst the seas be cast: 11 Our God, who is the Lord of hosts, 3 Though waters roaring make, And troubled be yea, though the hills is still upon our side; by swelling seas do shake. The God of Jacob, our refuge forever will abide. 4 A river is, whose streams do glad the city of our God; PSALM. XLVII. The holy place wherein the Lord most high hath his abode. 1 ALL people, clap your hands; to God with voice of triumph shout: 5 God in the midst of her doth dwell; 2 For dreadful is the Lord most high, nothing shall her remove: great King the earth throughout. The Lord to her an helper will, and that right early prove. 3 The heathen people under us he surely shall subdue; 6 The heathen rag'd tumultuously, And he shall make the nations the kingdoms moved were : under our feet to bow. The Lord God uttered his voice, The earth did melt for fear. 4 The lot of our inheritance 7 The Lord of hosts upon our side choose out for us shall he, doth constantly remain: Of Jacob, whom he loved weil, The God of Jacob's our refuge, ev'n the excellency. us safely to maintain. 5 God is with shouts gone up, the Lord 8 Come, and behold what wondrous works with trumpets sounding high. have by the Lord been wrought: 6 Sing praise to God, sing praise, sing Come, see what desolations praise; he on the earth hath brought. praise to our King sing ye. 9 Unto the ends of all the earth 7 For God is King of all the earth : wars into peace he turns: with knowledge praise express. The bow he breaks, the spear he cuts, 8 God rules the nations, God sits on in fire the chariot burns. his throne of holiness.
